#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:714
msgid ""
"Added `VTK_USE_WIN32_OPENGL` option to disable Win32 API in `VTK::"
"RenderingOpenGL2` on Windows. This enables OSMesa support on Windows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:716
msgid "Improved performance of `vtkTupleInterpolator`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:717
msgid ""
"Added new module providing `zSpace` support to VTK, implementing render "
"window, interactor style, camera, etc. Supports both the \"Core zSpace "
"API\" (legacy) and the \"Core Compatibility zSpace API\" (latest)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:720
msgid ""
"`vtkAxisActor2D` labels now use `UseFontSizeFromProperty`, which was "
"formerly used exclusively by the title."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:722
msgid ""
"`vtkImageResliceMapper` now fully supports oriented images, in the same "
"manner as `vtkImageSliceMapper`. This allows the display of arbitrary "
"oblique slices of oriented images, including those where the orientation "
"matrix has a negative determinant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:726
msgid ""
"Improved performance and consistency of `vtkRenderWindowInteractor::"
"ProcessEvents` across all platforms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:728
msgid ""
"`vtkCompositePolyDataMapper` can now color separate blocks with different "
"scalar arrays. To use this functionality, turn on `ScalarVisibility` and "
"select a `ScalarMode` and/or a `ColorMode`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:731
msgid ""
"Improved performance of `vtkContext2D` for rendering large numbers of points."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:732
msgid ""
"`vtkCompositePolyDataMapper` can now use separate lookup tables and "
"interpolation modes for different blocks in a composite dataset. You can "
"override lookup table and other related attributes like scalar interpolation "
"and scalar ranges. Refer to `vtkMapper` documentation. Here's a summary:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:736
msgid "`ScalarVisibility`: True/False"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:737
msgid ""
"`UseLookupTableScalarRange`: When true, the mapper shall import the range "
"from the lookup table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:739
msgid ""
"`InterpolateScalarsBeforeMapping`: Applies when mesh is colored using point "
"scalars. This flag decides whether point colors are sampled using texture "
"maps instead of interpolating colors on the GPU after scalars are mapped to "
"colors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:743
msgid ""
"`ColorMode`: Specifies whether to map scalars to colors or directly use the "
"scalars as RGB(A) values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:745
msgid "`ScalarRange`: Specifies a range of scalars for color mapping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:746
msgid "`LookupTable`: Specifies a lookup table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:747
msgid ""
"`vtkCompositePolyDataMapper` in VTK::RenderingCore has been improved to "
"efficiently render large datasets. It now performs as well as "
"`vtkCompositePolyDataMapper2` in the VTK::RenderingOpenGL2 module, which has "
"now been deprecated. This refactor has significantly impacted the following "
"VTK modules:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:751
msgid ""
"`vtkCompositePolyDataMapper` now has an API similar to "
"`vtkCompositePolyDataMapper2`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:753
msgid ""
"`vtkCompositeSurfaceLICMapper` derives `vtkCompositePolyDataMapper` instead "
"of `vtkCompositePolyDataMapper2`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:755
msgid ""
"The OSPRay module uses `vtkCompositePolyDataMapper` instead of "
"`vtkCompositePolyDataMapper2`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:757
msgid ""
"`vtkVtkJSSceneGraphSerializer` uses `vtkCompositePolyDataMapper` instead of "
"`vtkCompositePolyDataMapper2`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:759
msgid ""
"Added new `vtkOpenGLES30PolyDataMapper` supports polydata and composite "
"dataset rendering with OpenGL ES 3.0. If VTK was configured with "
"`VTK_OPENGL_USE_GLES=ON`, this mapper is an override for `vtkPolyDataMapper`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:762
msgid ""
"Fixed `vtkSurfaceLICMapper` crash when rendering lines as tubes or points as "
"spheres."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:763
msgid ""
"`vtkTextureObject` can now be used to create texture buffers on all OpenGL "
"implementations that support 2D textures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:765
msgid "Fixed `vtkCamera` CAVE bugs for head tracking and volume rendering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:766
msgid ""
"Fixed compositing artifacts when volume rendering in parallel with the "
"OSPRay raycaster. This fix adds a new `VolumeSamplingRate` parameter to "
"`vtkOSPRayRendererNode`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:769
msgid "`vtkPolarAxesActor` has a number of new features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:770
msgid ""
"Radial/polar axes and arc ticks are now customizable. "
"`SetRequestedNumberOfRadialAxes`, `SetRequestedDeltaAngleRadialAxes`, "
"`SetArcTickMatchesRadialAxes`, `SetRequestedNumberOfPolarAxes`, "
"`SetRequestedDeltaAnglePolarAxes`, `SetArcTickMatchesPolarAxes`, "
"`SetDeltaAngleMajor`, and `SetDeltaAngleMinor` are all new methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:775
msgid ""
"Tick size is now computed as a ratio of maximum radius by default. You can "
"specify a value for this ratio using `SetTickRatioRadiusSize`, default is "
"0.02."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:777
msgid ""
"You can now change polar arcs resolution per degree. See "
"`SetPolarArcResolutionPerDegree`, default is 0.2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:779
msgid ""
"Text offsets are now customizable with `SetPolarTitleOffset`, "
"`SetRadialTitleOffset`, `SetPolarLabelOffset` and `SetPolarExponentOffset`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:781
msgid ""
"`vtkMultiVolume` now supports RGBA volume inputs in a similar way to the "
"existing single-input volume rendering. When turning off the "
"`IndependentComponent` flag of the `vtkVolumeProperty` and providing 4-"
"components to the mapper values are interpreted as RGBA."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:785
msgid ""
"Added new gradient background modes. You can select from various gradient "
"background modes with `vtkViewport::SetGradientMode`. The following modes "
"are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:787
msgid ""
"`VTK_GRADIENT_VERTICAL` Background color is used at the bottom, Background2 "
"color is used at the top."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:789
msgid ""
"`VTK_GRADIENT_HORIZONTAL` Background color on the left, Background2 color on "
"the right."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:791
msgid ""
"`VTK_GRADIENT_RADIAL_VIEWPORT_FARTHEST_SIDE` Background color in the center, "
"Background2 color on and beyond the circle ellipse edge. Circle/Ellipse "
"touches all sides of the square/rectangle viewport."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:795
msgid ""
"`VTK_GRADIENT_RADIAL_VIEWPORT_FARTHEST_CORNER` Background color in the "
"center, Background2 color on and beyond the circle/ ellipse edge. Circle/"
"Ellipse touches all corners of the square/rectangle viewport. See gradient "
"background examples:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:800
msgid ""
"Fix incorrect values from `vtkOpenGLRenderWindow::GetZBufferData` in OpenGL "
"ES 3.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:801
msgid ""
"`vtkOpenGLRenderWindow::GetZBufferData` now returns the correct depth values "
"in OpenGL ES 3.0 where the depth component is typically only 24-bit wide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:804
msgid "Fix GPU Ray Cast Volume Rendering with `ModelTransformMatrix`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:805
msgid ""
"For CAVE environments, the `vtkCamera` class provides a "
"`ModelTransformMatrix` as a means of manipulating all the objects in a "
"scene.  However, actually using this matrix effectively changes the position "
"of the camera (or eye), which is used by the "
"`vtkOpenGLGPUVolumeRayCastMapper`. This issue prevented CAVE users from "
"interacting with volume data in the CAVE, as written up [here](https://"
"gitlab.kitware.com/paraview/paraview/-/issues/21471)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:813
msgid "This change fixes the gpu volume rendering mapper by removing from\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:814
msgid ""
"developers the responsibility to pass the cameraPos uniform so that it "
"matches the actual transformations applied to each vertex in the vertex "
"shader. Instead, the effective eye position in dataspace is computed "
"automatically. Furthermore, this is done on the cpu, saving a matrix/matrix "
"multiply and several matrix/vector multiplies in the fragment shader."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:819
msgid "Fix Off-axis stereo image separation issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:820
msgid ""
"Fix how the final transformation, T, described in \"Generalized Perspective "
"Projection\" is applied when doing off-axis projection.  This transform "
"encapsulates the viewpoint offset, and should be computed using the same eye "
"positions used to compute the rest of the projection matrix, but was "
"inadvertently computed using the single EyePosition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:826
msgid ""
"The result of the bug was that stereo images of an object were always a "
"fixed distance apart from each other, regardless of the objects location w.r."
"t. the screen, and regardless of the the eye position w.r.t. the object and "
"screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:831
msgid ""
"This change moves computation of the left/right eye into a new method "
"GetStereoEyePosition() and uses that from both the projection and view "
"transform computations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../release/_9.3-stripped.md:835
msgid ""
"Also adds a test to render three disks at different locations with respect "
"to the screen to ensure the stereo image pairs behave correctly."
msgstr ""

